# CropAbility documentation rules

## Location

All **project documentation** belongs under **`doc/`** or root **`README.md`**:

| Doc | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `doc/TODO.md` | Master checklist (`CA-*` IDs; historical `M1-*` in log); checkbox truth source |
| `doc/TODO_PROGRESS_LOG.md` | Dated engineering log (required for each closed item; see **Progress logging** below) |
| `doc/TODO_PROGRESS_SYNC.md` | Vault / GitHub sync mapping (Obsidian `3.CropAbility/`) |
| `doc/TESTING.md` | Pytest layout, markers, publish vs dev assets |
| `doc/RUST_DEVELOPMENT.md` | PyO3, Cargo features, maturin |
| `doc/PYTHON_DEVELOPMENT.md` | Python API; legacy PGL blocks are archive reference only |
| `README.md` | User-facing install and usage |

Do **not** create `README.md` or architecture notes under `src/test/` or `src/main/python/`.

## Language

Follow `english-only.mdc` for all doc text.

## Content alignment

When updating docs, reflect current architecture:

- Python host → Rust extension; no Java, no TorchScript, no `scripts/`.
- Single root `Cargo.toml`; tests in `src/test/python/`.
- Resources in `src/main/resources/`; models not vendored in repo.

Keep `doc/PYTHON_DEVELOPMENT.md` legacy PGL sections clearly labeled as historical, not the supported API.

## Progress logging

**When to log:** Add a new entry in `doc/TODO_PROGRESS_LOG.md` whenever you:

- Close an `M1-*` / `CA-*` item in `doc/TODO.md` (checkbox → `[x]`).
- Land a significant partial milestone that future readers need to reconstruct (multi-file feature, behavior change, or blocked follow-up).

Pair each closed checkbox with a **LogRef** in `doc/TODO.md` pointing to the log heading (e.g. `LogRef: 2026-05-21 / CA-2211-01`, or `LogRef: baseline rollup` when covered only by the rollup entry). See [`doc/TODO_PROGRESS_SYNC.md`](doc/TODO_PROGRESS_SYNC.md) for vault sync rules and `M1-*` → `CA-*` migration.

**Be as detailed as practical.** The log is the durable engineering record for vault sync and onboarding — prefer one thorough entry over several vague ones.

### Required fields (every entry)

Use the template in `doc/TODO_PROGRESS_LOG.md`. Each field must be **specific**, not placeholder text:

| Field | What to include |
|-------|-----------------|
| **Date** | ISO date (`YYYY-MM-DD`); add a second date if work spanned days. |
| **TODO ID/Title** | Exact ID(s) from `doc/TODO.md` plus the human title. |
| **Scope** | What problem was solved, acceptance criteria, and what was explicitly **out of scope**. |
| **Files Changed** | Concrete paths (not “various”); group by area (`src/main/rust/…`, `src/test/python/…`, `doc/…`). Note new vs modified vs deleted. |
| **Validation Steps** | Exact commands run (`pytest …`, `cargo test`, `maturin develop …`, CLI invocations) and **pass/fail** outcome; mention skipped steps and why (no GPU, no htslib, etc.). |
| **Outcome** | What now works differently; user-visible behavior; link to README / dev doc sections updated. |
| **Risks/Follow-ups** | Open items, known gaps, regressions, dependency pins, or IDs of related unchecked TODOs. |

### Strongly recommended (include when applicable)

- **Commits / PRs:** Short hash(es) or PR URL(s) that contain the work.
- **Design decisions:** Why this approach (e.g. Rust vs Python, CLI flag names) and alternatives rejected.
- **Before / after:** Prior behavior vs new behavior; breaking changes called out explicitly.
- **API / CLI surface:** New or changed public functions, PyO3 exports, subcommands, flags, defaults.
- **Test coverage:** New or updated test modules and markers (`native`, `gpu`, `slow`).
- **Performance / resource notes:** Build time, memory, GPU requirement, or benchmark snippets if relevant.
- **Environment:** Conda/pip/maturin/Cargo feature flags needed to reproduce validation.
- **Vault sync:** Whether `doc/TODO.md` checkbox and LogRef were updated in the same change.

### Anti-patterns (do not do)

- One-line entries (“fixed bug”, “updated docs”) without paths, commands, or outcome.
- “Files Changed: repo” or “Validation: tests pass” without naming files or commands.
- Closing a checkbox in `doc/TODO.md` without a matching log entry (unless `LogRef: vault` for vault-only historical items).
- Duplicating the entire diff — summarize **what** changed and **why**, with paths as anchors.
